10 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Form of ballot on retention for judicial officers. (1) If an incumbent
11 judge is the only candidate for a judicial office, the name of the incumbent judge must be placed on the official
12 ballot for the general election as follows:
13 Shall (insert title of officer) (insert name of the incumbent officer) of the (insert title of the court) of the
14 state of Montana be retained for another term?
15 (2) Following the question, provision must be made, subject to rules adopted pursuant to 13-12-
16 202, for a voter to indicate a "yes" or a "no" vote. The form must include the incumbent's political party
17 designation and may not include a write-in space for the office.
